3) https://www.explainthatstuff.com/how-mp3players-work.html 

IDEATE : 
The ‚ÄúDhun‚Äù web application is a simple and interactive music-filtering system designed to generate playlists based on user preferences. The user selects three inputs‚ÄîMood, Year Category, and Language‚Äîand the system generates a unique playlist link that matches the user‚Äôs emotions and taste. The project focuses on personalization and simplicity, offering an enhanced music discovery experience.

The Dhun project is an interactive web-based application designed to provide personalized music recommendations based on user preferences. The system allows users to select their mood, year range, and preferred language, and then dynamically generates a curated playlist link that matches their emotional and listening profile. Built using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript, the application offers a clean interface, responsive design, and a simple yet effective recommendation logic.
The core mechanism uses a JavaScript mapping structure to match user selections with predefined playlist URLs, enabling fast and accurate playlist retrieval without the need for a database. The project demonstrates the integration of front-end technologies to create a mood-adaptive music experience similar to modern streaming platforms.
This application is efficient, beginner-friendly, and highly extendable. With future enhancements‚Äîsuch as AI-based emotion detection, machine learning recommendations, and integration with music APIs‚Äîthe Dhun system has the potential to evolve into a fully personalized music recommendation engine. Overall, the project showcases how user interaction and simple logic can be combined to deliver an engaging and meaningful digital experience.


The main objective of the project is to:
Provide customized music recommendations.


Build a user-friendly interface for playlist selection.


Demonstrate how HTML, CSS, and JavaScript can be used together to create an interactive application.


Allow users to explore music based on emotional and demographic categories.




Hardware Requirements
Any device with a web browser (PC / Laptop / Mobile).


Software Requirements
Web browser (Chrome, Firefox, Edge)


Code editor (VS Code, Notepad++, Sublime)


Technologies Used
HTML5 ‚Äì for structure of the webpage


CSS3 ‚Äì for styling and layout design


JavaScript ‚Äì for dynamic behavior and playlist generation logic
Features of the System
 Mood Selection
Users can pick moods like Joyful, Sad, Romantic, Party, Workout.
 Year-Based Filtering
Three time periods are provided:
80‚Äì90


90‚Äì2000


2000‚Äì2025


 Language Selection
Supports English, Hindi, Marathi, and Punjabi.
 Interactive Playlist Output
A dynamic button appears only when a valid playlist is matched.
 Responsive & Clean UI
Designed using modern CSS (glassmorphism style) and adaptive layout for mobile and desktop screens.

ANALYSE:
Easy to use


No database required


Fully responsive


Customizable playlist links


Suitable for beginners and practical projects 

The ‚ÄúDhun‚Äù playlist generator successfully demonstrates how user preferences can be used to produce personalized music recommendations. Using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript, the project achieves a functional and visually appealing system that enhances the user‚Äôs listening experience.

User Mood Matters
Music preference is strongly influenced by mood.
 Examples:
Happy ‚Üí energetic songs


Sad ‚Üí slow or emotional songs


Angry ‚Üí calming tracks


Thus, mood-based personalization enhances user satisfaction.
2. Age Also Affects Music Choice
Different age groups prefer different genres and tempos:
Age Group
Music Preference
Teens
Pop, trending, rap
Young Adults
Lo-fi, romantic, EDM
Middle Age
Classics, retro
Seniors
Devotional, soft

So combining mood + age leads to more accurate recommendations.



Song Playback


System plays top-ranked song


Learns from user feedback (like/dislike)



3. Output
Mood-matched playlist


Age-appropriate music


Personalized experience


4 Advantages
Fully personalized music experience


Emotion-aware technology


Useful for stress relief and mental health


Suitable for entertainment systems and smart devices


