 CONCLUSION
The project ‚ÄúDhun ‚Äì Mood Based Playlist Generator‚Äù successfully demonstrates how a web application can provide personalized music recommendations using simple front-end technologies. By using HTML for structure, CSS for design, and JavaScript for logic, the system allows users to generate playlists based on their emotional state, preferred year range, and language.
The application is lightweight, responsive, and user-friendly. It removes the need to manually search for songs and instead provides instant curated playlists. The project highlights how conditional mapping and dynamic DOM manipulation can be used to build interactive solutions.
Overall, the project meets its objectives and offers a strong foundation for further expansion such as using APIs, artificial intelligence mood detection, and auto-generated playlists.

